<PageMeta category="Ontology" variant="warn" updated="Draft · Updated 2026-06-14" />

  <h1>Known issues</h1>

  <p class="lead">
    A completeness claim that conceals deferred work or defects is a provenance lie. This
    is the dated register of every known caveat in the OPDA PDTF ontology, each
    cross-referenced to the ODR that governs it. The important distinction throughout:
    <strong>none of these is a defect in OPDA's own materialised graph.</strong> They are
    consumer-side traps, by-design outcomes, a report-side miscount, and one item already
    resolved by a rename.
  </p>

  <nav class="callout callout--note" aria-label="On this page">
    <div class="callout__label">On this page</div>
    <ul style="margin: 0;">
      <li><a href="#register">The register (dated 2026-06-14)</a></li>
      <li><a href="#epc">Why the EPC cross-trip is not a model defect</a></li>
      <li><a href="#thin">Why thin profiles are by design</a></li>
      <li><a href="#ruleset">Why the ruleset is not an OWL 2 RL reasoner</a></li>
    </ul>
  </nav>

  <h2 id="register">The register <span class="muted">(dated 2026-06-14)</span></h2>
  <table>
    <thead><tr><th>Issue</th><th>Governing record</th><th>Status</th><th>Detail</th></tr></thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>EPC-certificate inference cross-trip</strong></td>
        <td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0028">ODR-0028</a> R3 / <a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0029">ODR-0029</a> R4</td>
        <td><span class="pill pill--info">Consumer-side</span></td>
        <td>
          A naive full-RDFS/OWL consumer mis-infers <code>EPCCertificate ⊑ Property</code>
          (because <code>currentEnergyRating</code> has <code>rdfs:domain</code>
          <code>Property</code>). <strong>OPDA's own Safe-Group closure excludes domain/range
          rules and does NOT produce this</strong> (<a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0025">ODR-0025</a> §R7); the round-trip exemplars
          validate against the Safe-Group closure. The model is correct — this is a trap a
          naive consumer sets for itself.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Thin overlay profiles</strong></td>
        <td>session-034 / <a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0010">ODR-0010</a></td>
        <td><span class="pill pill--ok">By design</span></td>
        <td>
          16 of 31 profiles bind 0 per-leaf shapes. Most overlay leaves are
          A/B/C/D/E/F treatments carried by <code>dct:subject</code> + <code>dct:source</code>,
          not per-leaf <code>sh:path</code> — profiles bind Category-G only. 224 bound / 1095
          GAPped across 28 forms; the GAP register is the deliberate, honest record of this.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong><code>oc1</code> / <code>llc1</code> held thin</strong></td>
        <td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0008">ODR-0008</a> / session-034 Q2</td>
        <td><span class="pill pill--ok">By design (re-open trigger)</span></td>
        <td>
          Authority-register extracts (Official Copy / Local Land Charges), not human-filled
          forms. Held thin until a named consumer issues a worked SPARQL query against a
          register leaf — at which point the binding is re-opened.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>SHACL-Core vacuous <code>sh:xone</code></strong></td>
        <td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0017">ODR-0017</a></td>
        <td><span class="pill pill--warn">Open (documented caveat)</span></td>
        <td>
          The committed non-conformant exemplar reads <code>conforms: true</code> under
          plain SHACL-Core. Correct validation requires <strong>pyshacl with
          <code>advanced=True</code></strong> (see <a href="/ontology/usage#validation">Consume
          the ontology</a>). Documented, not silent.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Ruleset is not OWL 2 RL</strong></td>
        <td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0029">ODR-0029</a> R5</td>
        <td><span class="pill pill--ok">Resolved (rename)</span></td>
        <td>
          <code>config/opda-rdfs-plus.rules</code> is a <strong>sound but RL-incomplete</strong>
          fragment (7 of the RL rules; omits domain/range/equality/functional/equivalence) —
          not an OWL 2 RL reasoner. Resolved by an honest rename + header; the rule logic is
          frozen.
        </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><strong>Category-C binning report miscount</strong></td>
        <td><a href="/modelling/odr/odr-0028">ODR-0028</a></td>
        <td><span class="pill pill--info">Report-only</span></td>
        <td>
          A report-side over-count in <code>descriptive-category-binning.json</code>; the
